body:
It is sometime not possible to directly pass a list to `passert.Equals` by using the `ellipsis` operator.
This PR adds a specialized Equals function for lists.

Example usecase: 
```golang
tests := []struct{
  given interface{}
  expected interface {}
} {
  {
    given: []int{1, 2}
    expected: []int{3}
  },
}
// [...]
got := Sum(scope, beam.CreateList(scope, test[0].given))
passert.EqualsList(scope, got, test[0].expected)
```

